results.title: The Name of the Game Is Mayhem!
results.description: DD saves the Invisible Girl from the Trapster, but in the ensuing battle, hurts his back as he takes down the villain; Foggy is asked to run for District Attorney; Debbie Harris is paroled from prison and contacts Foggy; Dr. Doom shows up.

results.title: Don't Look Now, But It's Dr. Doom
results.description: Doom captures Daredevil and switches bodies with our hero.

results.title: So Little Time To Save the World
With a Little Help From My Friends
results.description: Karen is on trial for killing a police officer and Mr. Fear is trying to manipulate things so that she will go to jail and DD will suffer a breakdown as a result.

results.title: Previously Unseen Cover Art for Daredevil #368!
Flying Blind Part 1: Stranger in a Strange Land
Flying Blind Part 1
results.description: Laurent Levasseur wakes up in a hospital room in France with fuzzy memories and fuzzy eyesight; He seems to be an agent on a mission but he isn't quite sure who he works for or what he is supposed to do; SHIELD agent Harlan knows that Laurent is really Matt Murdock, deep undercover with his memories reprogrammed, but Harlan is killed before he can give this information to anyone else; Matt has a new identity and is on his own in a foreign country with no support and no way to get back to his old life.

results.title: Flying Blind Part 2: All-Out Chaos in the Streets of France!
Flying Blind Part 2
results.description: Undercover agent Laurent Levasseur does not know that in his real identity he is either Matt Murdock or the costumed adventurer known as Daredevil and wonders why he has a compulsion to roam the streets of France wearing tights and fighting bad guys; Foggy begins to look for the missing Matt; Kingpin sets his sights on Laurent.

results.title: Flying Blind Part 3: Under the Gun
Flying Blind Part 3
results.description: Foggy and SHIELD begin to realize what has happened to Matt Murdock and exactly how much trouble he is in; Matt as Laurent finds himself facing off against Kingpin's goons.

results.title: Flying Blind Part 4: Face to Face with the Truth!
Flying Blind Part 4
results.description: During a battle with Kingpin and his henchmen, Laurent regains his memories of being Matt Murdock and Daredevil; SHIELD and Foggy finally catch up with Matt and he loses his temporary eyesight as he prepares to return to his normal life.

results.title: The Living Prison!
results.description: After a few battles and not a few episodes of identity confusion, DD and Doom are reverted back to their original bodies, but the FF doesn't know that.

results.title: Just One Good Story
results.description: Kingpin tries to frame a Middle Eastern man for terrorism so he can get his hands on a shipment of weapons; Matt defends the patsy and wins in court; DD takes on four of his deadliest foes to foil the Kingpin's scheme.

results.title: Introducing The Exterminator and the Super-Powered Unholy Three
results.description: DD tangles with the Unholy Three, little realizing that their new boss, the Exterminator, has developed a time displacement gun; Crashing a Nelson and Murdock double-date, the Three zap Debbie into oblivion for betraying their former boss, the Organizer.

items.name: Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (2003)
Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Killgrave, the Unbelievable Purple Man!
results.description: DD runs up against a purple man who can make anyone do what he wants just by suggesting it.

items.name: Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (2003)
Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (Trade Paperback)

results.title: The Fallen Hero
results.description: Throwing down with the Unholy Three, DD is zapped with the Exterminator's time displacment gun and zapped into limbo, possibly for eternity (or at least until next issue).

results.title: The Death of Mike Murdock
results.description: DD redturns from the time displacement limbo just in time to save Foggy from the Exterminator and the Unholy Three while killing off his Mike Murdock alter-ego in the process.

results.title: Nobody Laughs At the Jester
results.description: The Jester bursts onto the scene and is hired by Raleigh to take out the current candidate for D.A. Foggy Nelson; The "new" Daredevil stops the plot and the newest crown prince of crime.

results.title: In Combat With Captain America
results.description: Busted up over his breakup with Karen, DD takes it out on Captain America during a charity event.

results.title: I, Murderer
results.description: Jester frames DD by making it look like our hero killed the crime clown's alter-ego, Jonathan Powers, for daring to reveal Hornhead's identity to the world; Once the law is against him, Jester captures Daredevil for the police.

results.title: The Dismal Dregs of Defeat
results.description: With the police thinking he is a murderer, DD tries to avoid the law but is captured by the Jester and sent to jail.

results.title: The Final Jest
results.description: DD has to break out of jail to clear his name of a trumped up murder charge; Once old hornhead figures out the Jester set the whole thing up, he dresses as the Jester and appears on Carson to draw out the crime clown; Jester and DD battle as the plot concludes on live tv.

results.title: Farewell To Foggy
results.description: DD tries to save Foggy from Stilt-Man as the villain is trying to kill his portly companion before the upcoming election; Foggy is elected District Attorney and splits with Matt over a perceived slight by his former partner.

results.title: Daredevil Drops Outtt
results.description: Biggie Benson hires mad scientist Starr Saxon to send a killer robot after DD.

Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (Trade Paperback)

results.title: The Mysterious Masked Matador
results.description: A disgraced matador turns criminal to have his revenge on humanity; Daredevil stops the criminal's incessant cape waving.

items.name: Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (2003)
Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (Trade Paperback)

Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (Trade Paperback)

results.title: If In Battle I Fall
results.description: The Plastoid and DD duke it out until the giant robot is hurt and returns to his master; In the heat of battle with Hornhead, Starr accidentally sends the robot off to kill the man who hired him, Biggie Benson.

results.title: Run, Murdock, Run
results.description: While DD is battling his nefarious Plastoid robot, Starr Saxon invades Matt Murdock's apartment and finds out the he and Daredevil are on and the same; Determined to end his career as DD, Matt tries to patch things up with Foggy and Karen; Starr begins to hound Matt; Matt begins to have weak spells as doctors discover he is dying of radiation poisoning.

results.title: The Night of the Panther
results.description: DD is dying of radiation poisoning and Black Panther helps him rescue Karen from Saxon; Both the Panther and Saxon know DD's secret identity.

results.title: As It Was In the Beginning
results.description: Daredevil thinks back on his origins.

results.title: Call Him Fear
results.description: A new Mr. Fear challenges Daredevil to a public brawl and DD is branded a coward when he freaks out during the fight.

results.title: Cry Coward
results.description: Plagued by random phobias, DD has to overcome his weaknesses and take down a new Mr. Fear.

results.title: And Death Comes Riding
results.description: DD follows Karen home to Virginia to come clean about his feelings for her, but they both run up against a mysterious glowing horseman plaguing her family estate.

results.title: In the Midst of Life...!
results.description: With a little help from the Page's butler, DD defeats Death's-Head, only to find at the villain's death that he is Karen's father; At Paxton Page's funeral, DD reveals his secret identity to Karen.

results.title: Spin-Out On Fifth Avenue
results.description: Knowing that Matt is DD, Karen pressures him into give up his super-heroic lifestyle so they can be together; As DD is about to make a public announcement, Stunt-Master cycles in and crashes the party; Matt refuses to give up being Daredevil and Karen storms out.

results.title: Look Out, D.D.! It's Death to Tangle with the Torpedo!
The Torpedo Will Get You If You Don't Watch Out!
results.description: After Willie accidentally discovers his secret lair, Crime-Wave sends Torpedo to kill him, but DD steps in to save his old friend.

items.name: Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (2003)
Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Vol. I - 2nd Edition (1st) (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Trapped By the Fellowship of Fear
results.description: DD intrudes on a phony movie shoot where the Fellowship of Fear is robbing a bank and gets himself blasted by fear gas; Mr. Fear decides to flush DD out by creating a wax figure of Hornhead for his museum; DD and Foggy both get in a brawl with the Fellowship, and Foggy is injured; DD returns to the wax museum to put an end to the Fellowship.
